  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind feature\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\n`--resource` option in `kubectl create (cluster)role` does not support asterisk `*` as below:\r\n\r\n~~~\r\n# kubectl create clusterrole superrole --verb=get  --resource=*\r\nthe server doesn't have a resource type \"*\"\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nFollowing command works fine.\r\n\r\n~~~\r\n# kubectl create clusterrole superrole --verb=get  --resource=*\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nJust Run:\r\n\r\n~~~\r\n# kubectl create clusterrole superrole --verb=get  --resource=*\r\nthe server doesn't have a resource type \"*\"\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n\r\n~~~\r\n# kubectl version\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"10\", GitVersion:\"v1.10.0\", GitCommit:\"fc32d2f3698e36b93322a3465f63a14e9f0eaead\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2018-03-26T16:55:54Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.3\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"10\", GitVersion:\"v1.10.1\", GitCommit:\"d4ab47518836c750f9949b9e0d387f20fb92260b\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2018-04-12T14:14:26Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.3\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n~~~",
